 King Williams Town - Over 990 suspects were arrested over the past weekend, from 10 to 12 January, by King Williams Town police for various crimes. "Twenty-nine suspects were arrested for murder, 194 for assault (GBH), 35 for burglary, 11 for driving under the influence of alcohol or drugs, 32 for illegal possession of fire and ammunition," described police spokesperson, Captain Khaya Tonjeni. "In our concerted efforts to fight the primary drivers of crime like illegal dealing in alcohol, alcohol and drug abuse, twelve suspects were arrested for drinking in a public place while 27 were taken in for being drunk in a public place. "A total of 5 941 counterfeit goods were confiscated, 2 360 fake cigarettes, 2 800 fake money were seized." He added that 560 knives were also taken from various people. "Various operations were held Provincial Operation team at Libode and Ngqeleni where illegal taverns were closed down, while those who failed to comply were given fines. During these weeklong operations, about 1 051 litres of liquor was also seized." Capt Tonjeni said that a total of 2061.7kg of Dagga, 228g of Crystal Meth (Tik) and 21g of Mandrax powder was also seized by police. "All these suspects are expected to appear soon at different courts throughout the Province facing respective charges." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 